<dl id="n08126g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08126g">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08126g"> 126(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pater &amp; aves</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It is morally impossible that Lady Godiva&apos;s circlet of jewels could have been intended to count Ave Marias &hellip; the strings of beads were called &ldquo;paternosters&rdquo; because for a long time they were principally employed to number repetitions of the Lord&apos;s Prayer. <small> <a name="CECRA" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CECRA"><cite title="source">&ldquo;Coemgen&rdquo;, &ldquo;Rosary&rdquo; and &ldquo;Albigenses&rdquo;</cite></a> <cite a>Catholic Encyclopaedia</cite></a> (1911) XIII, &lsquo;Rosary&rsquo; 185b</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
